         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne Botanic Garden, ¶ 22 January 1867. ¶  ¶ You were so kind, esteemed Professor, to send me the last copies of your ¶  ¶ Mittheilungen ¶ , ¶ Mittheilungen aus Justus Perhes' geographischer Anst...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">67.01.22</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">To August Petermann</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="de">
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">Sammlung Perthes Archiv,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">SPA ARCH<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">PGM<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">328</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>Forschungsbibliothek Gotha der Universität Erfurt.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; "/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS annotation by Petermann: 'Erh. 23. März 1867' [Received 23 March 1867]. For a published version of this letter, see Voigt (1996), p. 84.</p>
               </note>Melbourne im bot. Garten</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">am 22 Jan 1867.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sie waren so gütig, verehrter Herr Professor, mir die letzten Blätter Ihrer Mittheilungen zu senden u ich habe Ihnen zu danken, dass Sie wiederum meines Namens glorreich erwähnen. Gewiss werde ich für die Erforschung der Polarregionen streben, die uns nahe liegen, sobald sich die erste günstige Gelegenheit bietet. Mitlerweile bin ich thätig die Durchforschung Australiens zu fördern. Mr Barnett, ein früherer Begleiter M'Intyres hat sich der Parthie angeschlossen. Sowie die Golfgegenden durchsucht sind soll sich die Parthie neu organisirt nach dem Süd-Westen wenden, u ich habe der Regierung Westaustraliens angerathen ein halb Dutz<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Dutzend?</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Kameele mit den Postdampfschiffen nach King George's Sound von Aden kommen zu lassen. So durch mehrfache Züge von Reisenden, stets mit diesen Thieren versehen, werden wir wohl die fruchtbaren Strecken u die Oasen des westlichen Theils des Continentes auffinden.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">Stets der Ihre</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne Botanic Garden,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">22 January 1867.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>You were so kind, esteemed Professor, to send me the last copies of your<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Mittheilungen</seg>,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Mittheilungen aus Justus Perhes' geographischer Anstalt</seg>.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and I must thank you, that once again you made laudable mention of my name.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See Petermann (1866) in which, after giving an account of the travails of the Ladies’ Leichhardt Search Expedition, Petermann paid tribute to M’s strenuous efforts in getting the expedition into the field, and to his efforts more generally in promoting Australian exploration.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I shall certainly pursue the exploration of the polar regions that are situated close to us, as soon as the first favourable opportunity offers. Mr Barnett, a former companion of M'Intyre, has joined the party.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Duncan McIntyre;<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Ladies' Leichhardt Search Expedition, 1865-6.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>As soon as the Gulf<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>regions<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn5" n="6">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Gulf of Carpentaria.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>have<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>been searched, the party is to be reorganized and will turn south-west. I have advised the Government of Western Australia<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn6" n="7">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to J.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Hampton, 27 December 1866 (in this edition as 66-12-27b).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>to have half a dozen camels brought from Aden to<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>King George's Sound<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn7" n="8">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>WA.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>by mail steamer. Thus, by travellers using different routes, always equipped with these animals, we ought to be able to find the fertile tracts and the oases in the western part of the continent.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="margin-left: 1.75in; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Always your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="margin-left: 1.75in; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. Mueller.</p>
         </div>
      </body>
   </text>
